# Generated / release-stamped files: on a merge conflict, ALWAYS take the
# INCOMING (committer's) version — never the local one.
#
# version.rb, value_bridge's version.rb, and share/mtimes.json are produced by
# the maintainer at release time (`rake bump:*`, recorded mtimes). The recorded
# mtimes in particular MUST be the committer's: setup restores them so mruby's
# mtime-driven build only rebuilds the files that actually changed in the
# release. If a stale LOCAL copy won (the old `merge=ours`), a user pulling an
# update would keep their own mtimes and mruby would rebuild EVERYTHING (minutes
# per update). So the committer's copy always wins.
#
# package.json is hand-edited by the maintainer (commands, capabilities) plus the
# bumped version — also the committer's authority, so `theirs` propagates new
# commands on update instead of dropping them on conflict (which `ours` did).
#
# The `theirs` driver must be registered once per clone (gem:build does this
# automatically; AGENTS.md has the manual one-liner):
#   git config merge.theirs.driver 'cp -f %B %A'
lib/mruby_lsp/version.rb                          merge=theirs
vendor/value_bridge/lib/value_bridge/version.rb   merge=theirs
share/mtimes.json                                 merge=theirs
editors/vscode/package.json                       merge=theirs
